<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="iddb9c4bd2-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06" identifier="/us/usc/t12/s1468c"><num value="1468c">§ 1468c.</num><heading> Separability</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">If any provision of this chapter, or the application thereof to any person or circumstances, is held invalid, the remainder of the chapter, and the application of such provision to other persons or circumstances, shall not be affected thereby.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="iddb9c4bd3-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06">(<ref href="/us/act/1933-06-13/ch64/s14">June 13, 1933, ch. 64, § 14</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/101/73/tIII/s301">Pub. L. 101–73, title III, § 301</ref>, <date date="1989-08-09">Aug. 9, 1989</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/103/343">103 Stat. 343</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
